  "canonical_definition": "Lexical Reachability is the metric that operationalizes the Token-Substrate Hypothesis as the gap between a model's cold-state distinguishability of a term against named near-neighbors and its post-introduction distinguishability after a single-sentence definition is provided in context, scored per (model × term × near-neighbor) cell.",
